						img.articlevertimg.center-block(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/e_auto_contrast,q_54:420,r_25/v1498676135/throwitintoaportal.jpg")
						h4.articleskilltext Throw It Into A Portal! is an Action card available in GRAVITY GIRL's deck. It has THROW, meaning that you'll need to destroy one of your Utilities as a cost for playing it. Played by itself, it lets you place one of your opponent's Utilities on top of their deck.  
					.col-md-6.articlecardpanel 
						h3.articlevertcardheading.gg-backgroundcolor barrage
						img.articlevertimg.center-block(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/e_auto_contrast,q_54:420,r_25/v1498676135/barrage.jpg")
						h4.articleskilltext Barrage is an Action card also available in GRAVITY GIRL's deck. It has THROW, meaning that you'll need to destroy one of your Utilities as a cost for playing it. Played by itself, it deal 2 damage to any one opponent or 4 damage if you've already played a THROW card previously this turn.	
				p.articletext These two work well together. Check this out...

				img(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/v1500588106/gganim1.gif").center-block

				p.articletext Throw It Into A Portal and Barrage are two of the THROW cards avaiable in Gravity Girl's deck. Both require you to destroy one of your own Utilities as a cost, but each have a different purpose. Throw It Into A Portal is great at getting rid of pesky Utilities while Barrage goes directly for your opponent. This versatility is GRAVITY GIRL's greatest strength, especially since you can further mix-and-match abilities by choosing which Utilities to destroy.

				p.articletext Let's look at another example...

				.row.articlecardrow.text-center
					.col-md-6.articlecardpanel
						h3.articlevertcardheading.gg-backgroundcolor javelin throw
						img.articlevertimg.center-block(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/e_auto_contrast,q_54:420,r_25/v1498676135/javelinthrow.jpg")
						h4.articleskilltext Javelin Throw is an Action card avaiable in the Gravity Girl deck. It has THROW, meaning that you'll need to destroy one of your Utilities as a cost for playing it. Played by itself, it deals 4 damage to any one Utility.
					.col-md-6.articlecardpanel
						h3.articlehorzcardheading.gg-backgroundcolor picnic table
						img.articlehorzimg.center-block(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/e_auto_contrast,q_54:420,r_25/v1498676135/picnictable.jpg")
						h4.articleskilltext Picnic Table is a Utility card available in the Gravity Girl deck. Played by itself, it does nothing waiting for you to destroy it. If you do, it deals 3 damage to any one opponent.

				p.articletext These two cards work quite well together. Let's walk through it! 

				img(src="http://res.cloudinary.com/jhi5/image/upload/v1500588106/gganim2.gif").center-block

				p.articletext Javelin Throw is a powerful card for dealing with Utilities. Dealing 4 damage will destroy 90% of all Utilities and Crossovers in the game. It also has Throw, meaning that we'll need to destroy a Utility in order to play it.

				p.articletext On the other hand, Picnic Table doesn't do anything. It doesn't have any Armor and can't Fight. Why play it? Picnic Table combines well with Throw cards. By choosing Picnic Table when using Javelin Throw, you will be able to deal 4 damage to a Utility and 3 damage to a player! That's 7 damage with only two cards!

				p.articletext Combining THROW cards with Utilties that like to be thrown is the key to mastering GRAVITY GIRL. GRAVITY GIRL is capable of switching between combo, defensive and offensive decks just by choosing different THROW cards! Want to play with GRAVITY GIRL without feeling lost in space? Gravity Girl can be difficult to deckbuild so don't be afraid to make tweaks. You could leave yourself empty-handed without a good mix of Utility and THROW cards!

